  "texts": [
    "The Hα spectra of a stellar source with the maximum absolute difference of wing-band mean flux greater than the threshold (such as the example shown in Figures 17a and 17b) are regarded to be inconsistent in the line wings.",
    "Only the stellar sources with the maximum absolute difference of wing-band mean flux less than the threshold are kept in our sample.",
    "C.2 Consistency of Hα profiles in the line center for the stellar sources with lower activity levels",
    "As described in Section 3.2.3, in order to recognize the stellar objects with consistent Hα profiles in the line center from the class of stellar sources with lower activity levels (I median Hα < 0.5), we sort the Hα spectra of multiple observations of each stellar source in the class by their I Hα index values, and calculate the correlation coefficients of the normalized spectral fluxes in a 3 Å-wide line-center band between the Hα spectrum with the smallest I Hα index value and other spectra with larger I Hα index values.",
    "Figure 18a gives an example of the MRS Hα spectra of a lower activity level stellar source (uid: G15979829169950; seven spectra in total) that show inconsistent profiles in the line center."
